best lasagne recipe out there can someone recommend a really flavorful beef lasagne recipe the worlds best lasagna meat sauce lb lean ground beef medium onions finely choppe stalks celery chopped cloves garlic minced oz tomato sauce cup red table wine lb hot italian sausage oz mushrooms finely chopped medium green pepper chopped oz tomato paste oz stewed tomatoes salt and pepper to taste tsp ea basil sage oregano rosemary tarragon tbsp coriander crushed tsp ea thyme cayenne pepper bay leaf tsp anis seeds crushed tsp celery seeds crushed tsp sugar filling large eggs beaten oz quark or low fat cottage cheese drained tsp pepper lb spinash lb low fat mozzarella cheese sliced lasagna noodles cooked lb grated low fat swiss cheese gruy are or emmanthal meat sauce brown the lean ground beef and the italian sausage in a large heavy frypan mash well to have a fine smooth sauce pour off all the fat transfer to a large kettle add some oil to the frypan and saut the vegetables until limp but not brown transfer to the kettle add the tomato paste tomato sauce and crushed italian tomatoes to the kettle with the wine herbs and spices simmer for hour taste and adjust seasoning add sugar if necessary comtinue simmering for hours or longer filling thoroughly wash spinach put in a double boiler and steam spinach until cooked but not overcooked drain and chop put into a medium bowl and add quark or low fat cottage cheese mix in large eggs add some salt and pepper if desired set aside grate swiss cheese and set aside slice mozzarella and set aside for a lasagna pan of x x inches you need lasagna noodles cook noodles in rapidle boiling salted water until just tender rinse under running water and set aside to assemble in the bottom of a lasagna pan x x in spoon a layer of sauce to coat the bottom lay down a row of noodles cover with some of the spinach mixture lay a row of noodles crosswise cover with some of the swiss cheese lay another row of noodles lengthwise cover with another layer of sauce repeat layering process until dish is full cover everything with a layer of mozzarella cheese and bake in an oven set at 'f until top is melted and lasagna is heated through this sauce is mild if you want more spice add some chili peppers with caution serve with a fresh salad and some fresh french or italian crusty bread enjoy Meatball Bagel Hot pot Sushi Mayonnaise Ricotta cheese Cuisine of Turkey Tamale Stock (food) Chile pepper Pancake Fish sauce Cuisine of Austria Donburi Coriander Italian beef B__chamel sauce Pot Noodle Sichuan Pepper Black pepper Garlic Chowder 